1. ryu_client.py — HTTP client that talks to the Ryu controller. Handles GET (telemetry) and POST (actions) with retry logic and error handling. All other modules use this to communicate with the network.

2. telemetry_parser.py — Takes the raw JSON from ryu_client.get_port_stats() and converts it into structured PortStatistics dataclasses, then builds a normalized 5-element numpy state vector [link1_util, link2_util, link3_util, packet_loss, traffic_load]. This is what the RL agent sees.

3. action_translator.py — Takes an integer action ID (0-4) from the RL agent and converts it into the corresponding Ryu REST API call via ryu_client. Returns an ActionResult with success/failure info.

4. mock_ryu_server.py — Fake Ryu controller running on localhost:8080. Returns randomized but realistic port/flow stats for GET requests and accepts POST actions. Used for testing without a real SDN network.

5. reward.py — Multi-objective reward function with 4 components:
   R_util     = -mean(utilizations)²           (penalizes high usage)
   R_loss     = -packet_loss × 100             (heavy penalty for drops)
   R_balance  = 1/(1+std(utilizations))        (rewards even distribution)
   R_congestion = -5 if any link > 80%         (congestion penalty)
   Final reward clipped to [-10, 10].

6. sdn_env.py — Gymnasium environment that wraps the LIVE network. Uses ryu_client + telemetry_parser + action_translator + reward. Each step(): execute action → wait 2s → collect telemetry → compute reward. Requires mock_ryu_server or real Ryu to be running.

7. mock_env.py — Gymnasium environment that simulates the network OFFLINE. No server needed. Simulates:
   - Congestion that builds when no action is taken
   - Traffic shifting between links when routing actions are chosen
   - Rate limiting that reduces/increases overall utilization
   - Packet loss that correlates with congestion (higher loss when any link > 80%)
   Used for RL training without any real network or mock server.


Data flow so far:

=== LIVE mode (sdn_env.py + mock_ryu_server) ===
mock_ryu_server (port 8080)
       ↓ GET /stats/port
  ryu_client.get_port_stats()
       ↓ raw JSON
  telemetry_parser.build_state()
       ↓ np.array([5])
  agent decides action_id  ← (not built yet)
       ↓ int (0-4)
  action_translator.execute(action_id)
       ↓ uses ryu_client POST
  mock_ryu_server receives command
       ↓ wait 2s (stabilization)
  reward.compute_reward(state)
       ↓ float

=== OFFLINE mode (mock_env.py, no server needed) ===
  mock_env.reset()
       ↓ random initial state
  agent decides action_id  ← (not built yet)
       ↓ int (0-4)
  mock_env.step(action_id)
       ↓ simulates traffic + congestion + loss
  reward.compute_reward(state)
       ↓ float


